<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=12961&amp;highlight=#12961">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopi ... ght=#12961</a><!-- m --><br /><br />This was a previous thread about the same subject. My Eprom eraser is just a bare bulb and a fixture about $25 altogether. Of course you shouldn't stare at it while it is on but routine caution should prevent burns. I stay out of the room or cover it while it is on. In hospitals where I work they have sterilizing lights which must be UVC and they are on all the time. However I don't recommend exposing yourself.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=236">Lloyd Gordon</a> — Sat Jun 17, 2006 7:58 am</p><hr />
