<title type="html"><![CDATA[Question for building an EPROM Eraser]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1659&amp;p=14214#p14214"><![CDATA[
I have some 27cxxx chips that I would like to erase. Recently I came across some breakfast cerial thing.. where you get a free UV light pen. The pen writes in special ink and then on the otherside there's a UV light which you can shine on the writing to see it.<br /><br />Anyway, enough rambling, my question is, if I hook up the light (it's as big as a NES LED or a tiny bit bigger) to a constant DC power circuit and have it directly over the EPROM in a dark room, is it likely to erase the EPROM? I can get more than one to create an array if need be. It would be a good cheap way to make one, and it doesn't seem as dangerous as the other EPROM erasers out there.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=367">joe78</a> — Fri Jun 16, 2006 7:31 pm</p><hr />
